Hi, we're just wondering is there a way to prevent the 'Enter' key to submit the form while on Edit or Transition Screen?

Our business users feel that the 'Enter' key behaviour is a bit too inconsistent in the Edit/Transition screen, depending on the field type of where the last cursor is located. For example, if the field is multi-text then Enter key means new line, while if if it is a single-text field then it will submit the form. Similarly with single select list field Enter key means opening the drop down list, however with Label field it will submit the form. If the cursor is in the number field then it will submit the form same like in user picker.

Since the behaviour of the key always changing depending on the field type, we are concerned that users will find it too confusing since they could inadvertently submit the form while trying to do something else. To make it more consistent can we take away the functionality to submit the form when pressing 'Enter' key in Edit/Transition screen?

